1
00:00:05,819 --> 00:00:08,298
Very often,
if not most often,

2
00:00:08,298 --> 00:00:10,020
if not all the time,

3
00:00:10,357 --> 00:00:12,657
whom we’re attached to,

4
00:00:12,657 --> 00:00:16,675
we’re projecting something
onto another person.

5
00:00:17,046 --> 00:00:19,217
[Hungry Heart]

6
00:00:19,217 --> 00:00:23,059
We’re so deeply attached
to a person, place or thing,

7
00:00:23,059 --> 00:00:26,859
but where’s the attachment?
It’s not in them,

8
00:00:26,859 --> 00:00:30,539
the attachment is in us,
it’s some conceptual thing.

9
00:00:30,539 --> 00:00:38,779
They symbolically represent something
to us that we feel we cannot break that,

10
00:00:38,779 --> 00:00:43,851
or we’ll somehow become undone,
be unsafe, full of anxiety,

11
00:00:43,851 --> 00:00:46,601
have a meaningless life,
whatever it might be.

12
00:00:46,601 --> 00:00:50,799
But really, 
the seed is within us.

13
00:00:50,799 --> 00:00:56,601
So in one place we’re told,
that laulyam, that hṛt-rogam,

14
00:00:56,601 --> 00:01:00,269
that heart disease,
that mundane attachment to

15
00:01:00,269 --> 00:01:03,362
persons, places,
things of this world,

16
00:01:03,362 --> 00:01:11,044
that will be an obstruction 
on the path of progressive devotion.

17
00:01:11,044 --> 00:01:14,364
Then, in its counter-śloka,

18
00:01:14,364 --> 00:01:16,597
Krishna-bhakti-rasa-bhavita-matih

19
00:01:16,597 --> 00:01:19,321
kriyatam yadi kuto ’pi labhyate

20
00:01:19,367 --> 00:01:22,704
tatra laulyam mulyam ekalam

21
00:01:22,704 --> 00:01:31,433
janma-koti-sukritair na labhyate
(Cc: Madhya, 2.8.70).

22
00:01:31,695 --> 00:01:35,842
Here, now he’s saying
laulyam is good.

23
00:01:35,842 --> 00:01:38,898
He just said laulyam
is what will spoil devotion,

24
00:01:38,898 --> 00:01:41,060
attachment, 
this type of mundane …

25
00:01:41,060 --> 00:01:45,813
Now suddenly there’s
some other type of laulyam

26
00:01:45,813 --> 00:01:48,583
that’s the real thing,
and if you’ve got that,

27
00:01:48,583 --> 00:01:54,036
that’s your ticket, that’s the
purchase price of Kṛṣṇa consciousness.

28
00:01:54,036 --> 00:01:58,777
So then it means, oh, ultimately,
desire, hankering, attachment,

29
00:01:58,777 --> 00:02:00,950
all these things,
they’re not bad.

30
00:02:00,950 --> 00:02:11,094
It’s towards whom
and where that is located.

31
00:02:12,220 --> 00:02:16,838
Deep in the heart’s core?

32
00:02:18,562 --> 00:02:23,098
He’s saying,
“Janma-koṭi-sukṛtair na labhyate”,

33
00:02:23,098 --> 00:02:27,100
you won’t get 
this type of hankering

34
00:02:27,100 --> 00:02:33,022
for ten million births
of doing the right thing.

35
00:02:33,022 --> 00:02:34,723
That’s amazing.

36
00:02:34,723 --> 00:02:42,384
Ten million lifetimes of doing 
the right thing won’t give you this.

37
00:02:42,736 --> 00:02:46,911
Where will you get what’s required,
this laulyam, this hankering?

38
00:02:47,826 --> 00:02:51,178
… Laulyam can also be described
as hankering,

39
00:02:51,178 --> 00:02:55,703
as Guru Mahārāj would say,
earnest sincere hankering, not curiosity.

40
00:02:55,703 --> 00:02:59,340
We should not confuse
being curious about something

41
00:02:59,340 --> 00:03:05,137
with genuine hankering for
connection with it substantially.

42
00:03:05,137 --> 00:03:10,417
So, that devotee,
actually Shyamananda Prabhu,

43
00:03:10,417 --> 00:03:16,378
he said,
“How to get this hunger?”

44
00:03:16,378 --> 00:03:18,936
That was the word 
being used.

45
00:03:18,936 --> 00:03:24,017
And Guru Mahārāj said,
“Associate with the hungry.”

46
00:03:24,017 --> 00:03:28,539
And we know
from being with Śrila Gurudev,

47
00:03:28,539 --> 00:03:32,417
sometimes Vaiṣṇav Maharaj—Shrutashrava Prabhu
would point this out,

48
00:03:32,417 --> 00:03:34,956
even if we had just taken a feast,

49
00:03:34,956 --> 00:03:39,475
if Gurudev started describing prasādam,
different preparations,

50
00:03:39,475 --> 00:03:41,681
he described them 
in such a way

51
00:03:41,681 --> 00:03:46,626
that he awakened
your appetite again.

52
00:03:46,626 --> 00:03:49,740
Even if you’d just eaten,
suddenly you were …

53
00:03:49,740 --> 00:03:53,218
he stimulated your appetite.

54
00:03:53,218 --> 00:03:56,409
And that’s what we’re told,
that will happen in association

55
00:03:56,409 --> 00:03:59,190
with those who have 
some genuine hunger

56
00:03:59,190 --> 00:04:02,532
and appetite 
for Kṛṣṇa consciousness.

57
00:04:02,532 --> 00:04:07,527
If you can’t follow what they’re saying,
serve them,

58
00:04:07,527 --> 00:04:11,051
and what’s in them
will be transferred to you

59
00:04:11,051 --> 00:04:15,248
like an infectious disease
but in a good way.

60
00:04:15,248 --> 00:04:22,135
That’s why they say, “Make sure you
clean the glasses and sterilise everything”,

61
00:04:22,135 --> 00:04:24,049
and we’re saying 
the opposite of that,

62
00:04:24,049 --> 00:04:26,554
if someone’s infected
with Kṛṣṇa consciousness,

63
00:04:26,554 --> 00:04:29,004
take their remnants
and you‘ll be infected too,

64
00:04:29,004 --> 00:04:30,969
and that’s a good thing.

65
00:04:30,969 --> 00:04:33,131
And serve them,
and what’s in their heart,

66
00:04:33,131 --> 00:04:35,419
which is not only
the love and affection,

67
00:04:35,419 --> 00:04:43,969
but the hunger, hankering,
attachment, if you will,

68
00:04:43,969 --> 00:04:49,449
attachment to Kṛṣṇa,
to devotion, to devotees,

69
00:04:51,833 --> 00:04:55,410
that will be awakened
in your own heart.

70
00:04:55,457 --> 00:04:57,324
Hare Kṛṣṇa.

